WEBVTT

00:02.403 --> 00:04.572
**

00:04.605 --> 00:06.340
Hello.

00:06.374 --> 00:07.908
What?
Are those moving boxes?

00:07.941 --> 00:09.143
Is somebody moving out?!
Let me help.

00:09.177 --> 00:10.578
No. No.

00:10.611 --> 00:12.012
It's stuff
I was storing here

00:12.046 --> 00:13.847
because I didn't have room
in my apartment,

00:13.881 --> 00:16.150
but now since I'm moving
into Neville's place,

00:16.184 --> 00:18.086
I got to figure out
what to bring.

00:18.119 --> 00:19.620
No one
ever moves out.

00:21.455 --> 00:22.923
Well, you make it
too nice.

00:22.956 --> 00:24.392
Moldy shower curtains,

00:24.425 --> 00:26.727
four different kinds
of soap chunks smashed into one.

00:26.760 --> 00:28.429
Nobody's leaving that.

00:29.697 --> 00:32.032
Hey!
You look nice.

00:32.066 --> 00:35.035
I'm meeting some friends
at the bar for happy hour.

00:35.069 --> 00:37.205
Are they meeting you
in your coat?

00:37.238 --> 00:40.274
'Cause it seems like
that's where all the
food and drinks are.

00:40.308 --> 00:42.876
Well, even happy-hour prices
are kind of high.

00:42.910 --> 00:45.179
Usually, I'll flirt with a guy
so he buys me drinks,

00:45.213 --> 00:47.681
and then I'll shimmy out the
bathroom window and head home,

00:47.715 --> 00:49.450
but the place tonight
is at a rooftop bar,

00:49.483 --> 00:52.420
and I don't want to fall 20
stories for a pumpkin pale ale.

00:55.123 --> 00:57.525
There's a lot of things
you can take from this house --

00:57.558 --> 00:59.627
books, vegetables,
Jackie.

01:01.162 --> 01:02.930
But if you think I'm spending
the rest of my night

01:02.963 --> 01:06.066
with these people sober,
you are sadly mistaken.

01:06.100 --> 01:07.401
Gimme.

01:08.236 --> 01:09.036
Hm!

01:09.069 --> 01:11.205
Gimme.

01:11.239 --> 01:13.541
I guess I'm back
to flirting for drinks.

01:13.574 --> 01:15.743
You're not getting
any younger. I'd go.

01:18.179 --> 01:20.648
So how come it took you so long
to move in with Neville?

01:20.681 --> 01:22.216
He's an old-fashioned guy.

01:22.250 --> 01:23.917
He felt like living together
before marriage

01:23.951 --> 01:25.819
would make God cry.

01:25.853 --> 01:29.223
And yet he had no problem
with all the premarital sex.

01:29.257 --> 01:31.325
Single guys have
their own religion.

01:31.359 --> 01:34.828
Oh, I tell ya, I tell ya,
God would be inconsolable

01:34.862 --> 01:36.497
if he saw what we were doing
every night

01:36.530 --> 01:39.066
before I said bye-bye
and headed home.

01:39.099 --> 01:42.102
Are you excited to be
moving in with your fella?

01:42.136 --> 01:44.104
Oh. Yeah.
Absolutely.

01:44.138 --> 01:45.639
This is the first time
I'm living with somebody

01:45.673 --> 01:48.008
because we want to
be together, you know?

01:48.041 --> 01:50.411
Not because he stole my key
while I was asleep

01:50.444 --> 01:52.913
and made a copy
at Home Depot.

01:52.946 --> 01:55.115
Oh, my God.

01:55.149 --> 01:56.850
There's stuff from
all different parts

01:56.884 --> 01:59.753
of my life
in these things.

01:59.787 --> 02:01.289
[ Chuckles ]

02:01.322 --> 02:04.592
Oh, my God!
My old service taser!

02:04.625 --> 02:08.128
I was looking for this
the last time my mom visited.

02:08.162 --> 02:11.332
Wait! This was just sitting
in the closet for years?

02:11.365 --> 02:13.301
Relax. It was in a box.
It was taped shut.

02:13.334 --> 02:14.968
Oh, there you go.

02:15.002 --> 02:17.205
No kid has ever gotten
through Scotch tape.

02:17.238 --> 02:19.507
That's why they use it on
liquor cabinets and pool gates.

02:21.008 --> 02:23.377
Wow. Well, no wonder
my box was so heavy.

02:23.411 --> 02:25.379
It's filled with books.

02:25.413 --> 02:27.281
Copies of the book
I self-published,

02:27.315 --> 02:30.784
"Lessons from a Life Coach."

02:30.818 --> 02:32.386
How many of these
did you sell?

02:32.420 --> 02:34.822
Oh, that's not important.

02:34.855 --> 02:36.224
If I helped
one person --

02:36.257 --> 02:37.525
Got it. One.

02:39.927 --> 02:43.063
Hey! You got Roseanne's
plastic cow creamer.

02:43.096 --> 02:45.132
[ Laughs ]
She spent like eight years

02:45.165 --> 02:46.534
looking all over the place
for this thing.

02:46.567 --> 02:48.669
I know.
You know what?

02:48.702 --> 02:51.905
Sometimes I even
helped her look for it.

02:51.939 --> 02:54.808
I was gonna slip it into
her casket at the funeral,

02:54.842 --> 02:57.411
but then I thought
I can't let go of that memory

02:57.445 --> 02:59.247
of watching her wander
through the house going,

02:59.280 --> 03:00.681
"Where is that
damn thing?"

03:00.714 --> 03:02.483
[ Laughs ]

03:02.516 --> 03:03.751
You know, for
a former life coach,

03:03.784 --> 03:05.253
you're kinda sadistic.

03:09.357 --> 03:10.491
[ Door opens ]

03:10.524 --> 03:11.592
[ Television turns on ]

03:13.026 --> 03:14.595
Hey.
Hmm.

03:14.628 --> 03:16.697
Why do you look so happy?
You know where you are, right?

03:16.730 --> 03:18.499
[ Chuckles ]

03:18.532 --> 03:20.167
I also know where
we're going tonight.

03:20.200 --> 03:22.436
I got tickets to that
new Italian movie.

03:22.470 --> 03:24.438
The one with the sex, huh?
And the food?

03:24.472 --> 03:26.907
And the screaming
and the smoking and the --

03:26.940 --> 03:28.776
Well, you know.
An Italian movie.

03:28.809 --> 03:31.078
Yeah, if I wanted all that,
I'd just hang out

03:31.111 --> 03:33.381
in the alley
behind the high school.

03:33.414 --> 03:35.783
And to keep the
international theme going,

03:35.816 --> 03:37.918
I got a reservation
at the best French restaurant

03:37.951 --> 03:39.753
in Kane County --
Le MaÃ®tre D'.

03:39.787 --> 03:41.522
You know why they call it that,
don't you?

03:41.555 --> 03:43.357
The last restaurant
was called Le MaÃ®tre D'

03:43.391 --> 03:45.259
and they didn't feel like
changing the sign.

03:47.595 --> 03:49.530
Well, that is so sweet,

03:49.563 --> 03:51.465
but you don't have to do
all that for me.

03:51.499 --> 03:53.534
Oh, come on.
It's gonna be fun.

03:53.567 --> 03:55.369
You know
what else is fun?

03:55.403 --> 03:57.438
Getting cozy and snuggling up
right here on the couch.

03:57.471 --> 03:59.206
And you know what?

03:59.239 --> 04:01.942
We will take control of the
remote for the whole night.

04:01.975 --> 04:03.777
Dan: No, you won't!
Yes, we will!

04:06.914 --> 04:08.215
Alright, well,
what about dinner?

04:08.248 --> 04:09.717
I already
took care of it.

04:09.750 --> 04:13.287
At some point, Kenny will be
dropping a contactless delivery

04:13.321 --> 04:16.657
of vegan enchiladas
right at our doorstep.

04:16.690 --> 04:18.392
Oh, he's pulling
out of a weed store,

04:18.426 --> 04:20.060
so we might not get
all of our food,

04:20.093 --> 04:21.929
but some of it's
gotta get here.

04:23.331 --> 04:26.233
Well, we can still have
an international night of sorts,

04:26.266 --> 04:29.236
I guess, and before we go
to our Italian movie,

04:29.269 --> 04:31.639
Kenny will be high
on Jamaican kush,

04:31.672 --> 04:33.907
and then
we'll offend Mexico

04:33.941 --> 04:37.678
by eating what you pretend
are enchiladas.

04:37.711 --> 04:40.781
I am down
with all of that,

04:40.814 --> 04:43.517
except for
one small tweak.

04:43.551 --> 04:45.252
We change
going to a movie

04:45.285 --> 04:47.421
to not going
to a freakin' movie --

04:47.455 --> 04:50.157
Pardon my French. Oh, wait.
There's your international.

04:50.190 --> 04:56.464
**

04:56.497 --> 05:03.103
**

05:03.136 --> 05:09.643
**

05:09.677 --> 05:12.646
-- Captions by VITA --

05:12.680 --> 05:14.014
"The Conners" is recorded

05:14.047 --> 05:15.449
in front of
a live studio audience.

05:15.483 --> 05:17.117
Hmm.

05:17.150 --> 05:18.519
What happened?

05:18.552 --> 05:21.455
Uh, you fell asleep
just as Mrs. Doubtfire's

05:21.489 --> 05:25.325
[laughing] fake boobs
caught fire from the stove.

05:25.359 --> 05:28.529
[ Sighs ] I've seen that movie
three times.

05:28.562 --> 05:31.699
Fiery boobs are funny
maybe twice.

05:31.732 --> 05:33.801
Look,
I can't waste my life

05:33.834 --> 05:36.236
sleeping on this couch
anymore, you know?

05:36.269 --> 05:40.173
I need some stimulation,
some things that make me think.

05:40.207 --> 05:42.342
Geez. Since when did
everything have to be

05:42.376 --> 05:44.545
so highbrow,
artsy-fartsy for you?

05:44.578 --> 05:46.514
We've always sat around
and vegged out on the couch.

05:46.547 --> 05:49.517
Yeah, but I --
[ Groans ]

05:49.550 --> 05:52.386
I need to be around
creativity, you know?

05:52.420 --> 05:54.722
I-I-I don't write anymore,

05:54.755 --> 05:57.491
and I work at a hardware store
all day long.

05:57.525 --> 05:59.493
And your dad went on
the other day for 20 minutes

05:59.527 --> 06:02.362
about toggle bolts
versus anchor bolts,

06:02.396 --> 06:04.364
and at one point, I looked
over at the rat poison

06:04.398 --> 06:07.468
and I was like, "Oh, man!
If only I had the guts."

06:11.439 --> 06:14.241
Well, I'm --
I'm so sorry.

06:14.274 --> 06:16.276
You know, I didn't know
that you still missed

06:16.309 --> 06:18.579
the magazine so much.
Yeah.

06:18.612 --> 06:21.014
Okay. How is this?

06:21.048 --> 06:23.784
Let's check the guide
for a foreign movie

06:23.817 --> 06:25.218
that we can watch
tomorrow night,

06:25.252 --> 06:27.254
and we can eat
a foreign snack.

06:27.287 --> 06:30.023
Popcornopolis.
That's Greek, right?

06:30.057 --> 06:32.893
You're not listening to me,
okay?

06:32.926 --> 06:34.528
There's things going on
out there

06:34.562 --> 06:36.396
that I want to be a part of.

06:36.430 --> 06:38.231
Okay, fine.

06:38.265 --> 06:40.934
I-I mean, I want you to be
happy, so pick --

06:40.968 --> 06:42.603
pick something you want to do.
Anything.

06:42.636 --> 06:44.772
Great. Okay.

06:44.805 --> 06:46.940
Uh, they're doing
"Romeo and Juliet"

06:46.974 --> 06:48.876
at The Pickled Playhouse
in Elk Grove Village

06:48.909 --> 06:50.478
this weekend.
Absolutely not.

06:50.511 --> 06:52.746
Every one of those words
sounds awful.

06:52.780 --> 06:54.615
[ Chuckles ]
Come on. It's fun.

06:54.648 --> 06:56.383
Look, one of
the cast members

06:56.416 --> 06:59.252
has to do shots every five
minutes until they're drunk,

06:59.286 --> 07:02.456
and then they start screwing up
their lines and improvising,

07:02.490 --> 07:05.225
and the -- the whole play
becomes something else entirely.

07:05.258 --> 07:08.562
Does it become
something I want to watch?

07:08.596 --> 07:12.299
[ Both laugh ]

07:12.332 --> 07:14.935
Look, I'm going,
with or without you.

07:14.968 --> 07:17.304
Okay. Fine. I'll go.

07:17.337 --> 07:19.439
But I don't understand why
we can't just grab some beers

07:19.473 --> 07:20.641
and rent
"The Lion King."

07:20.674 --> 07:22.610
That's like "Hamlet"
with a gassy warthog.

07:24.545 --> 07:26.413
Neville: I really like
that cow creamer.

07:26.446 --> 07:29.182
Jackie: Yeah, I just hope it
goes with the rest of the stuff

07:29.216 --> 07:31.685
that you got in the --
[ Pig snorts ]

07:31.719 --> 07:34.121
Well, the...

07:34.154 --> 07:36.990
cow's gonna
fit right in.

07:37.024 --> 07:38.425
What's all this about?

07:38.458 --> 07:40.928
These are guys
that need extra care.

07:40.961 --> 07:42.663
I usually stay late
at the clinic for that,

07:42.696 --> 07:44.932
but I want us to be able
to spend time together,

07:44.965 --> 07:46.767
so I just
brought them home.

07:46.800 --> 07:49.503
Are any of these animals
dangerous?

07:49.537 --> 07:51.772
Oh. Gosh, no.
[ Chuckles ]

07:51.805 --> 07:54.474
Depends on
what you mean by that.

07:54.508 --> 07:57.110
Well, like,
is that gonna get out

07:57.144 --> 07:58.646
and try and eat me
while I'm sleeping?

07:58.679 --> 08:01.181
No, no, no.
These are all pets.

08:01.214 --> 08:03.316
Although the pig was pulled out
of the slaughterhouse line

08:03.350 --> 08:07.888
at the last minute, so
sometimes he screams at night.

08:07.921 --> 08:11.859
So, um, this is all probably
gonna be for probably,

08:11.892 --> 08:15.729
like -- like,
probably like a week?

08:18.866 --> 08:21.835
Yeah, maybe, but now
that we're living together,

08:21.869 --> 08:25.472
I want us to establish a good
work-life balance, you know?

08:25.505 --> 08:27.975
I know it's a little
Doctor Dolittle-y,

08:28.008 --> 08:30.578
but there will probably
be some patients here

08:30.611 --> 08:31.745
for the foreseeable future.

08:31.779 --> 08:32.880
Oh. Okay.

08:32.913 --> 08:34.014
[ Pig squeals ]
Wow.

08:34.047 --> 08:35.849
Hm. [ Chuckles ]

08:35.883 --> 08:36.984
[ Macaw squawks ]

08:37.017 --> 08:38.586
Oh, there's
that thing, too.

08:38.619 --> 08:41.555
Oh, man. Yeah.

08:41.589 --> 08:44.324
That'll probably
go on all night [chuckles]

08:44.357 --> 08:47.561
so I think somebody
probably needs some codeine.

08:47.595 --> 08:49.196
Yeah.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

08:49.229 --> 08:51.098
I think
that's Mrs. Dolittle!

08:56.937 --> 08:59.907
Macaw: Where's my doctor?
I need a doctor.

08:59.940 --> 09:03.276
Sounds like somebody
lives with a hypochondriac.

09:03.310 --> 09:06.346
And you need to go...there.

09:06.379 --> 09:07.414
[ Pig grunts ]

09:07.447 --> 09:10.751
Hey, hey!
I live here, too, okay?

09:10.784 --> 09:12.419
Oh, you want it
over here?

09:12.452 --> 09:13.921
There.

09:13.954 --> 09:15.756
[ Pig grunts ]
Give it a rest.

09:15.789 --> 09:17.557
You've been screaming
all night long.

09:17.591 --> 09:19.793
We've all been through stuff!
Move on!

09:19.827 --> 09:21.028
[ Knock on door ]

09:21.061 --> 09:23.263
Macaw: Where's my doctor?
Uh-oh. I need a doctor.

09:23.296 --> 09:24.932
And suddenly it was night.

09:27.100 --> 09:28.301
Hey!
Hey.

09:28.335 --> 09:29.803
I brought the rest
of your life-coach books.

09:29.837 --> 09:32.806
Oh.
I thought the sewer
was backing up outside,

09:32.840 --> 09:35.275
but the smell
is coming from in here.

09:35.308 --> 09:37.477
Yeah, the vet tech guy
who cleans up,

09:37.510 --> 09:38.879
he's running
a little late.

09:38.912 --> 09:40.614
I wanted to light
a scented candle,

09:40.648 --> 09:43.350
but I think there's too
much methane in this room.

09:44.618 --> 09:46.386
What is happening here?

09:46.419 --> 09:48.922
Oh, it's actually
kind of romantic.

09:48.956 --> 09:50.624
Neville's bringing home
his patients

09:50.658 --> 09:52.059
that need extra care
at night

09:52.092 --> 09:54.061
so he can spend
more time with me.

09:54.094 --> 09:56.429
Maybe it's worth spending
a little less time with him

09:56.463 --> 10:00.000
not to have to watch that lizard
eat the skin he just shed.

10:00.033 --> 10:01.669
Oh, no, no.
It's not that bad.

10:01.702 --> 10:03.170
He's actually
really friendly.

10:03.203 --> 10:04.938
Oh.
Don't reach in, though.

10:04.972 --> 10:07.340
He's real attached
to that dead skin.

10:07.374 --> 10:09.176
If you touch it,
he moves like lightning.

10:09.209 --> 10:10.978
[ Gasps ]

10:11.011 --> 10:13.246
You have to put a stop
to this right now!

10:13.280 --> 10:15.248
You tell Neville
this is your house, too.

10:15.282 --> 10:16.650
Macaw:
Uh-oh! I need a doctor!

10:16.684 --> 10:18.786
You're supposed to
be asleep!

10:18.819 --> 10:20.788
[ Pig grunts,
macaw squawks ]

10:20.821 --> 10:22.622
It's like living
in a See 'N Say.

10:23.957 --> 10:25.859
I'm just not comfortable
telling Neville

10:25.893 --> 10:27.427
what he can do
in his own house.

10:27.460 --> 10:30.030
I mean, you know,
this happens all the time.

10:30.063 --> 10:33.533
You move in with a guy,
and he's got an old recliner

10:33.566 --> 10:35.803
or a traumatized pig
with night terrors,

10:35.836 --> 10:39.206
and, y-you know,
you just live with it.

10:39.239 --> 10:40.607
Talk to your husband!

10:40.640 --> 10:42.175
Yeah, I guess
you're right.

10:42.209 --> 10:44.544
Hey, while you're here,
I promised Neville

10:44.577 --> 10:46.446
I would give Betsy
a suppository.

10:46.479 --> 10:48.515
I need you
to hold her back legs.

10:48.548 --> 10:49.683
Which one's Betsy?

10:49.717 --> 10:52.019
If I tell you,
you won't do it.

10:55.188 --> 10:57.791
Romeo: [ Slurring ] Thy kinsmen
are no stop to me...

10:57.825 --> 11:01.995
Okay. Now, Romeo's had
14 shots in an hour.

11:02.029 --> 11:04.397
Now it's gonna get
crazy.

11:04.431 --> 11:07.367
This is the high culture you
were so desperately craving?

11:07.400 --> 11:08.902
[ Laughs ]

11:08.936 --> 11:10.337
With love's light wings

11:10.370 --> 11:13.741
did I o'er-perch
these walls, that --

11:13.774 --> 11:15.308
That's it.
I'm tapping out.

11:15.342 --> 11:16.376
[ Laughs ]

11:16.409 --> 11:17.878
We can tap out?
Cool. Let's go.

11:17.911 --> 11:20.047
No, no. It's not over.
This is the best part.

11:20.080 --> 11:22.149
This is when he's
gonna make some poor fool

11:22.182 --> 11:23.550
take his place onstage.

11:23.583 --> 11:26.386
You're up,
my good man!

11:26.419 --> 11:28.488
[ Applause ]

11:28.521 --> 11:30.090
Yeah!

11:31.091 --> 11:33.927
I shall not profess love
to such an unworthy suitor.

11:33.961 --> 11:36.864
I've been on "CSI: New Orleans."
I'm out.

11:36.897 --> 11:38.265
Oh.

11:38.298 --> 11:40.934
We need a Juliet!

11:40.968 --> 11:43.403
You!

11:43.436 --> 11:46.206
The one trying to make yourself
as small as possible.

11:46.239 --> 11:48.441
You're Juliet.

11:48.475 --> 11:51.178
[ Audience chanting "Juliet!" ]

11:51.211 --> 11:53.680
Oh, no, no, no.
Pick somebody else, please.

11:53.713 --> 11:56.249
Oh, come on.
Loosen up. Come on.

11:56.283 --> 11:58.418
Be hilariously bad, and
everyone will have a good laugh.

11:58.451 --> 12:01.088
Oh, now that I know I'll be
humiliated, I'd love to stay.

12:01.121 --> 12:03.523
Oh, well, I'm sorry
it's not as exciting

12:03.556 --> 12:05.625
as checking your Jitterbug
for messages

12:05.658 --> 12:07.427
and falling asleep
to "Blue Bloods."

12:07.460 --> 12:08.862
Oh, so I'm old now?

12:08.896 --> 12:10.397
You're becoming
your father.

12:10.430 --> 12:12.065
No, my father would have
never allowed himself

12:12.099 --> 12:13.400
to be dragged here.

12:13.433 --> 12:15.869
You said you wanted
to make me happy.

12:15.903 --> 12:16.970
Yeah, well,
that was a mistake

12:17.004 --> 12:18.405
that I will never
be making again.

12:18.438 --> 12:20.407
You know what? I'm done
going out altogether.

12:20.440 --> 12:22.109
Look out, Romeo.

12:25.478 --> 12:27.314
Where is this opening?!

12:31.351 --> 12:32.886
Where's Ben?

12:32.920 --> 12:35.155
Uh, he's staying
at his place tonight.

12:35.188 --> 12:36.623
Ohh.

12:36.656 --> 12:39.259
Whatever it is,
work it out.

12:39.292 --> 12:42.796
I'm not building you two a house
just to destroy my health.

12:42.830 --> 12:44.731
My hammer hand
is frozen into a shape

12:44.764 --> 12:46.800
that only works
for holding a beer.

12:49.436 --> 12:52.172
I think we can both agree
that you have a beer hand

12:52.205 --> 12:53.974
that occasionally
holds a hammer.

12:55.876 --> 12:58.011
Yeah, but it's no good
for cooking and cleaning,

12:58.045 --> 13:00.848
so I reckon you two squatters
will have to help with that.

13:02.883 --> 13:03.984
Oh.

13:09.823 --> 13:11.558
Oh, reach me the remote,
would ya?

13:14.294 --> 13:16.629
Oh. Damn it.
I got a crick.

13:16.663 --> 13:18.098
Oh.
Lean away from it.

13:18.131 --> 13:19.032
Okay.

13:21.734 --> 13:23.103
There we go.
Oh, yeah.

13:23.136 --> 13:25.005
Thank you.

13:25.038 --> 13:26.706
There you go.
Okay.

13:26.739 --> 13:28.308
Man: ...had a hose
that didn't kink

13:28.341 --> 13:30.677
and leak every time
you tried to use it?

13:30.710 --> 13:32.812
Oh, you know, you can
skip the commercials.

13:32.846 --> 13:34.814
I kinda like 'em.

13:36.483 --> 13:37.951
Yeah.
Actually, I do, too.

13:37.985 --> 13:39.286
...as soon as you
turn the water...

13:39.319 --> 13:41.621
Oh, I wouldn't mind
having one of those hoses

13:41.654 --> 13:43.156
that shrivels up when
you turn the water off.

13:43.190 --> 13:45.025
That's cool.

13:45.058 --> 13:48.896
I'd buy one if I could
get two for the same price.

13:51.164 --> 13:52.465
Wait for it.

13:52.499 --> 13:53.466
Two for the price of one!

13:53.500 --> 13:54.935
Nice!
Nice!

13:58.205 --> 14:00.040
Announcer:
...in the forecourt...

14:01.441 --> 14:02.675
Uh-oh.

14:05.045 --> 14:07.080
What?

14:07.114 --> 14:08.748
Well,
Ben might be right.

14:08.781 --> 14:11.351
He says
I'm becoming you.

14:11.384 --> 14:13.053
Oh, which me?

14:13.086 --> 14:15.722
The devil-may-care man
about town...

14:15.755 --> 14:18.358
or the guy that coasts
downhill to save gas?

14:19.893 --> 14:23.663
Well, he -- he thinks
I'm getting old and boring.

14:23.696 --> 14:26.499
Oh, it sounds like
the coasting guy.

14:26.533 --> 14:28.435
Look, there's
no shame in that.

14:28.468 --> 14:30.570
You have a family,
you work hard,

14:30.603 --> 14:33.006
and eventually,
your couch becomes

14:33.040 --> 14:36.176
your big, cushiony friend
that really gets you.

14:36.209 --> 14:37.844
But, I mean,
is that so bad?

14:37.877 --> 14:39.846
Not if you're married to
one of those anti-couchers

14:39.879 --> 14:41.548
that believes the hype.

14:44.617 --> 14:45.919
What hype?

14:45.953 --> 14:48.788
That there's a whole
interesting world out there.

14:48.821 --> 14:52.459
Louise badgers me to get out
and listen to live music

14:52.492 --> 14:53.927
or go to some art fair.

14:53.961 --> 14:56.463
I bitch about it the whole time,
but the truth is,

14:56.496 --> 14:58.265
I'm really happy
to have someone in my life

14:58.298 --> 15:01.368
to pull me off
of this couch sometime.

15:01.401 --> 15:04.471
Wow. So you love Louise
more than this couch.

15:04.504 --> 15:06.073
That is not
where my money was.

15:09.076 --> 15:12.079
Otherwise, you realize
life has passed you by

15:12.112 --> 15:14.914
and you're not
really living it.

15:14.948 --> 15:18.551
**

15:18.585 --> 15:20.087
[ Television playing ]

15:24.091 --> 15:26.293
Oh. [ Chuckles ]
I'll get him to move.

15:26.326 --> 15:28.395
Alfonso just does that
to get my attention.

15:28.428 --> 15:29.796
He's such a diva.

15:31.764 --> 15:33.967
Hey, Neville, how about

15:34.001 --> 15:36.303
let's turn off the TV
and just talk?

15:36.336 --> 15:37.837
Sure. Yeah.

15:37.870 --> 15:39.472
While we are talking,

15:39.506 --> 15:43.043
I am going to give this guy
a little me time.

15:45.778 --> 15:49.249
You know, ferrets are one
of the few animals that can go

15:49.282 --> 15:54.087
into a rabbit hole head-first
and come out head-first.

15:54.121 --> 15:56.623
One conversation ends,
another begins.

15:58.391 --> 16:02.129
Neville, um, I get that you're
bringing all these guys home

16:02.162 --> 16:03.663
because you want to
spend more time with me,

16:03.696 --> 16:06.166
but you're not really
spending more time with me.

16:06.199 --> 16:07.534
Oh. [ Scoffs ]

16:07.567 --> 16:09.169
Didn't we have fun
cleaning the earwax

16:09.202 --> 16:12.639
out of that chinchilla
together?

16:12.672 --> 16:14.974
Well, I thought Fernando
was a little more bitey

16:15.008 --> 16:17.144
than appreciative,
but the point is

16:17.177 --> 16:19.279
that we're spending a lot
of time with the animals

16:19.312 --> 16:21.481
and we're not getting
any private time.

16:21.514 --> 16:24.551
I know, but all this keeps life
pretty interesting, doesn't it?

16:24.584 --> 16:26.019
Interesting is a puppy.

16:26.053 --> 16:28.388
All this -- This is
a documentary that ends

16:28.421 --> 16:31.391
with the neighbors going,
"Well, we saw that comin'."

16:34.261 --> 16:37.397
We don't need all of this
to make our life interesting.

16:38.998 --> 16:40.900
But maybe we do.

16:40.933 --> 16:43.236
I don't understand.

16:43.270 --> 16:46.306
When we were dating
and we ran out of things to say,

16:46.339 --> 16:49.376
it was always just, "Goodbye.
See you tomorrow."

16:49.409 --> 16:53.380
But you're the first person
I've actually ever lived with.

16:53.413 --> 16:55.748
I -- [ Sighs ]

16:55.782 --> 16:57.550
I don't know
if I'm interesting enough.

16:57.584 --> 16:59.352
[ Gasps ] Neville!

16:59.386 --> 17:02.189
I-If I run out of things to say,
you're just gonna see

17:02.222 --> 17:05.258
this kind of boring,
awkward guy staring at you.

17:05.292 --> 17:06.726
Are you kidding me?

17:06.759 --> 17:09.062
You're, like, the most
interesting person that I know.

17:09.096 --> 17:11.498
And do you honestly think
that I would stop loving you

17:11.531 --> 17:13.933
if there's a lull
in the conversation?

17:13.966 --> 17:18.371
Well, not if there's
an adorable ferret in my lap!

17:18.405 --> 17:21.941
Okay, you don't have to worry
about silence with me.

17:21.974 --> 17:25.044
If you don't have anything
to say, it's okay.

17:26.613 --> 17:28.948
See?
I have nothing to say!

17:28.981 --> 17:31.351
Silence doesn't mean
that there's something wrong.

17:31.384 --> 17:33.120
It's like music,
you know?

17:33.153 --> 17:35.255
There's the notes,
there's the space in between,

17:35.288 --> 17:39.859
but you got to have them both
to make a beautiful song.

17:39.892 --> 17:41.361
You think
we make good music?

17:41.394 --> 17:43.230
Yeah, I do,
but we've got to get rid

17:43.263 --> 17:45.732
of all of these
backup singers.

17:49.569 --> 17:51.104
And I called the office.

17:51.138 --> 17:52.705
Some of these guys
are just being boarded.

17:52.739 --> 17:54.574
They're not even sick.
Neville!

17:54.607 --> 17:57.277
You had me put a suppository
in a duck

17:57.310 --> 17:59.646
that was, like,
basically on vacation.

18:02.315 --> 18:04.451
She doesn't really need them.
She just likes them.

18:05.952 --> 18:08.788
**

18:08.821 --> 18:10.089
Ben: Hey.

18:11.191 --> 18:12.792
Hey.

18:13.926 --> 18:15.228
You sleep okay?

18:15.262 --> 18:16.763
Yeah, yeah. Fine.

18:16.796 --> 18:18.064
I just came by
to get your dad.

18:18.097 --> 18:20.333
We're gonna finish up
some plumbing at the new house.

18:20.367 --> 18:23.436
We have a working bathroom now,
but the walls aren't up,

18:23.470 --> 18:25.472
so if you're
in the middle of things

18:25.505 --> 18:28.708
and you see a car coming,
it's a lot of pressure.

18:34.381 --> 18:36.449
Okay.
I'll just say it.

18:36.483 --> 18:39.118
Um, I'm sorry about
what happened at the play.

18:40.787 --> 18:42.789
Yeah, after you left,
they, uh --

18:42.822 --> 18:46.593
they picked me
to play Juliet.

18:46.626 --> 18:48.861
And I played her
more strong than pretty.

18:51.864 --> 18:53.833
I'm sorry
I missed that...
[ Chuckles ]

18:53.866 --> 18:55.968
...is something
you're supposed to say.

18:56.002 --> 18:57.537
[ Laughs ]

18:57.570 --> 19:00.173
Anyway, you're right. I-I --
Sometimes I need a little push

19:00.207 --> 19:02.475
to get out of the house,
so thank you.

19:02.509 --> 19:04.977
Oh.
I appreciate that.

19:05.011 --> 19:08.047
Alright. So how's this?

19:08.080 --> 19:11.218
We commit to going out
at least two nights a week.

19:11.251 --> 19:12.652
Mm-hmm.

19:12.685 --> 19:14.687
On my night,
we do an activity

19:14.721 --> 19:17.457
that normal people do,

19:17.490 --> 19:19.292
and on your night,

19:19.326 --> 19:23.363
we do some pretentious,
insufferable artsy thing

19:23.396 --> 19:26.666
that makes me wish
I was dead.

19:26.699 --> 19:29.402
Okay, so I get some creativity
to feed my soul

19:29.436 --> 19:31.037
and it annoys
the hell out of you?

19:31.070 --> 19:32.239
Oh, I'm so in.

19:32.272 --> 19:34.341
Okay.
Don't get excited.

19:34.374 --> 19:35.708
I got some rules
about your night.

19:35.742 --> 19:37.877
[ Groans ] Such as?

19:37.910 --> 19:41.381
No audience participation
of any kind,

19:41.414 --> 19:45.184
only one thing a year with
the word "festival" in it,

19:45.218 --> 19:47.354
no cover bands...
[ Sighs ]

19:47.387 --> 19:49.956
...and, no, I do not want to
"see all the cool 'merch.'"

19:51.891 --> 19:55.895
But I love my "Hamilton"
three-corner hat.

19:55.928 --> 19:57.564
And if you hadn't
worn it to bed,

19:57.597 --> 19:59.566
we wouldn't be having
this conversation.

20:03.035 --> 20:04.904
Well, what if I wear it
on my head next time?

20:07.206 --> 20:11.644
**

21:00.627 --> 21:01.561
[ Falsetto voice ]
All are punished, then this

21:02.429 --> 21:05.164
of Juliet and her Romeo.

21:05.197 --> 21:07.066
Ohh!

21:07.099 --> 21:09.836
Hey, hey! That dagger's
not as happy as we are,

21:09.869 --> 21:11.338
'cause you finally
stopped talking!

21:11.371 --> 21:13.773
[ Laughter ]
Yeah, hey!

21:13.806 --> 21:17.143
I was a better Juliet,
and I have a beard!

21:17.176 --> 21:19.979
I had to help
give a duck a suppository,

21:20.012 --> 21:21.548
and this is worse!

21:23.716 --> 21:26.185
[ Normal voice ] That's my
family. They came to support me.

21:26.218 --> 21:27.119
Hey!
